{# ── Chapter: Takeaway ── #}
<section class="case-chapter" data-chapter="takeaway">
  <h2>Remember</h2>
  <div class="case-takeaway">
    <h3>Key takeaways</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <div class="tone-junior">font-display: swap prevents invisible text but causes layout shift when the custom font arrives — it trades one bad UX for another.</div>
        <div class="tone-mid">Metric-matched fallback fonts (size-adjust, ascent-override, descent-override) make the FOUT invisible by matching the fallback dimensions to the custom font.</div>
        <div class="tone-staff">Use screenspan.net/fallback or fontpie CLI to generate metric-override values — don't hand-tune them, the math is precise and tooling is reliable.</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="tone-junior">Preload critical fonts with &lt;link rel="preload"&gt; — this shortens the time to swap so fewer users see the fallback font at all.</div>
        <div class="tone-mid">font-display: optional is the CLS-safe choice for non-critical fonts — it never swaps after the initial short block period, guaranteeing zero CLS.</div>
        <div class="tone-staff">Measure font-induced CLS in CrUX with source attribution — Chrome 108+ labels CLS shift sources, making font-vs-image-vs-other breakdown visible in real user data.</div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
